   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">It is important to understand how terms are used when working with Apttus Customer Incentive Manager.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <table class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Term</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Program Manager</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">To create an account or product-specific programs, update and align program qualifications, create programs from other programs, manage program lifecycles.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Product</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">A product or service that can be sold on its own as a standalone item, an option of other products, or as part of a bundled product.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Schedules</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">To run a process and to update various statuses on program schedules and programs.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Monitoring Processes</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Administrators can manage and review scheduled jobs and job status on the Monitor Processes page.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Calendars</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">To configure a fiscal calendar that consists of period types.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Settings</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Settings enable Administrators to configure existing program sub-types for Qualification and Benefits, and Participant pages based on program type, program sub-type, and program status.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Product Groups</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Product Groups is an option that allows you to combine the multiple products and categories from existing product hierarchy to evaluate a different set of products together.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Products and Categories</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">To define a dynamic combination of products and categories within the application</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Custom Product Group</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Custom Product Groups (CPG) are defined as product groups which are created at the time of program creation and allows you to combine multiple products and categories to evaluate a different set of products together.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
